Class Driver

  • java.lang.Object
    • game.Driver

  • public class Driver
extends java.lang.Object
    This class represents a driver on the road in the Compounded game. Total time spent: George - 2 hours, Joshua - 2 hours.
    Version:
    1.0 May 16, 2014., 2.0 - May 23, 2014 - No changes made., 3.0 - May 30, 2014 - Complete Driver class rewrite, it now works as intended., 4.0 - June 6, 2014 - No changes made., 5.0 - June 12, 2013 - Method relocation for better organization.
    Author:
    George Lim., Joshua Yuan.

    • Constructor Detail

      • Driver

        public Driver(java.lang.String newName,
      java.lang.String newDescription,
      int newLane,
      java.lang.String newElement,
      java.awt.Image car)
        Constructor that specifies the name, description, lane, element, and car of a driver. If null is passed in as a paramter for Image, a random car will be given to this Driver. The if structure checks if car has a null reference.
        Parameters:
        newName - String reference: Contains the new name of this Driver.
        newDescription - String reference: Contains the new description of this Driver.
        newLane - int: Contains the new lane of this Driver.
        newElement - String reference: Contains the new element associated with this Driver.
        car - Image reference: Contains the new car of this Driver. If the value of car is null, a random car will be assigned to this Driver.
